snippet.textDisplay: I need to defend my darling Whatburger a little: you really can't judge them based on how they taste as takeout. As you noticed, they are juicy and the longer they sit, the more wet they become. You really need to eat in the restaurant as things come out from the kitchen. Also, Whataburger's whole deal is they customize your burgers so you get it "just the way you like it". So if a burger needs mayo or sauce, you just add it. The best sandwich, you didn't get: Monterrey Burger or Whataburger Chicken Sandwich. Beware: those are very wet. Not ideal for takeout. Gotta eat it either right in the parking lot or at the restaurant.
